sheet.description:
You ignore difficult terrain, have advantage on initiative rolls, and on your first turn in combat you have advantage on attack rolls against creatures that have not yet acted. Additionally when traveling
            for an hour or more, you gain the following benefits; Difficult terrain doesn’t slow your group’s travel, Your group can’t become lost except by magical means, If you are traveling alone, you can move stealthily at a normal pace.,
             when you forage, you find twice as much food as you normally would, while tracking other creatures, you also learn their exact number, their sizes, and how long ago they passed through the area.
